article.headline: Valparaiso 69, UCF 52
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Urule Igbavboa scored 15 points and grabbed 14 rebounds, and Michael Rogers had 10 points and 11 rebounds as Valparaiso beat Central Florida 69-52 Tuesday night. Erik Buggs scored 11 for the Crusaders (2-0), who shot 46.3 percent from the field compared with the Knights' 30.4 percent. Jermaine Taylor had 18, including 8-of-17 from the field, to pace Central Florida (1-1). A.J. Rompza scored 10. Valparaiso led 30-21 at halftime. Valpo's largest lead was by 23 with 8:25 left in the game. The Crusaders outscored the Knights 24-10 in the paint in a game that included just one lead change.
